description:
In order to plan for a sprinkler system, we have to determine how many sprinkler heads we can have in each phase or zone. A phase or a zone would be the number of sprinklers you are running at a time. In this video there are 4 sprinklers that are running at one time so that would be 1 phase. If we want to know how many heads we can install we would need to know the flow rate of the water or the gallons per minute that are flowing from the water source. In this case we have 5 gallons of water in 20 seconds. To calculate the gallons per minute (GPM) we would divide 5 by 20 and multiply by 60 (5/20*60 = 15 GPM). At a flow rate of 15 GPM we can comfortably place 4 heads per zone if it requires 3 GPM per head or 7 if the sprinkler head needs 2 GPM. We can figure out the number of heads by the GPM required to run them and the GPM coming from the water source.
There are two main types of water sprinkler systems for the garden. Drip irrigation and overhead sprinklers. Drip irrigation systems are used to slowly release water to crops and flowers and are great to reserve water usage. In this video we used an overhead irrigation system because that is what the homeowner chose. The sprinkler head is a pop-up head. It is buried at ground level and the head pops up to water the area around the head. This particular head was adjusted to spray half of the circumference of the head and sprays out at 180 degrees from the head
The sprinkler system can be beneficial to water the garden and can be turned on for a little over an hour every other day depending on the climate and soil type. When you install a sprinkler system you would free up more time to focus on other aspects of the garden. The garden needs water and if there is not enough rain then the gardener would have to water by hand, or they can run a hose out to the garden with a sprinkler head at the end.
A timer can be placed at the base of the sprinkler system for an automatic watering system. This would free up even more time and add to the convenience of a self-sufficient garden. There are many different types of timers that could be used depending on the application.
We hope that this proves beneficial for you in your desire to begin or continue to have a self-sufficient garden.
